							travellers and others alike). &nbsp;<br> <br> This idea
							was greeted with mixed reactions by his industry friends. The
							reactions went from “you cannot cut out the middleman, aka the
							commission-based paid travel agent”, “travellers will never pay
							for such a service”. And then there were the instant supporters
							of the idea, and Marc Geissbühler, former VP of Switzerland’s
							largest tour operator Hotelplan who was so convinced of the idea
							that he became an investor and co-founder of
							Travel(Switzerland) AG. A company that was incorporated in
							August 2021. The decision was taken that the marketplace would be
